title: Josephine Omaka
text:
Josephine Ada Omaka (born 29 November 1993) is a Nigerian <a href="Sprint%20%28running%29">sprinter</a> and hurdler. She competed at local and international competitions in athletics representing Nigeria.
Career.
Josephine Ada Omaka started her career as a junior <a href="Sprint%20%28running%29">sprint runner</a> and hurdler in Nigeria where she competes in various local competitions. She won major competitive gold medals at the <a href="2011%20African%20Junior%20Athletics%20Championships">2011</a> and <a href="Athletics%20at%20the%202010%20Summer%20Youth%20Olympics">2010 Summer Youth Olympics</a> in <a href="Sport%20of%20athletics">athletics</a> at 100 metres events and also sparticipated at The women's 4 × 100 metres relay at the <a href="2012%20World%20Junior%20Championships%20in%20Athletics">2012 World Junior Championships</a> in Athletics which was held at the Estadi Olímpic Lluís Companys on 13 and 14 July, she also won the <a href="2009%20African%20Junior%20Athletics%20Championships">2009 African Junior Championships</a> event in the category 100 metres and another silver at the Nigeria <a href="100%20metres">4*100 m</a> relay in <a href="African%20Championships%20in%20Athletics">2009 competition</a> with <a href="Margaret%20Benson">Margaret Benson</a>, <a href="Goodness%20Thomas">Goodness Thomas</a> and <a href="Wisdom%20Isoken">Wisdom Isoken</a>. Furthermore, she participated in the African 4 × 400 m relay team that won silver medals at the <a href="Athletics%20at%20the%202010%20Summer%20Youth%20Olympics">2010 Summer Youth Olympics</a> with <a href="Nkiruka%20Florence%20Nwakwe">Nkiruka Florence Nwakwe</a>, <a href="Izelle%20Neuhoff">Izelle Neuhoff</a> and <a href="Bukola%20Abogunloko">Bukola Abogunloko</a>.
